{"abstract":[{"text":"Returns the depth of the stack of calls to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.dispatch","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] on any ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":" in the current thread.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maindepth()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"mainDepth"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That is, when called from the top level, it gives ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"text":". When","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"called from within a callback from [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.iteration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(or [method"},{"code":"GLib.MainLoop.run","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], etc.) it returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"text":". When called from within","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a callback to a recursive call to [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.iteration"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2"},{"type":"text","text":". And so forth."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is useful in a situation like the following:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Imagine an extremely simple ‘garbage collected’ system."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["static GList *free_list;","","gpointer","allocate_memory (gsize size)","{","  gpointer result = g_malloc (size);","  free_list = g_list_prepend (free_list, result);","  return result;","}","","void","free_allocated_memory (void)","{","  GList *l;","  for (l = free_list; l; l = l->next);","    g_free (l->data);","  g_list_free (free_list);","  free_list = NULL;"," }","","[...]","","while (TRUE);"," {","   g_main_context_iteration (NULL, TRUE);","   `free_allocated_memory()`;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This works from an application, however, if you want to do the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thing from a library, it gets more difficult, since you no longer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"control the main loop. You might think you can simply use an idle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function to make the call to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"free_allocated_memory()"},{"type":"text","text":", but that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t work, since the idle function could be called from a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recursive callback. This can be fixed by using [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.main_depth"},{"text":"]","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["gpointer","allocate_memory (gsize size)","{","  FreeListBlock *block = g_new (FreeListBlock, 1);","  block->mem = g_malloc (size);","  block->depth = g_main_depth ();","  free_list = g_list_prepend (free_list, block);","  return block->mem;","}","","void","free_allocated_memory (void)","{","  GList *l;","  ","  int depth = g_main_depth ();","  for (l = free_list; l; );","    {","      GList *next = l->next;","      FreeListBlock *block = l->data;","      if (block->depth > depth)","        {","          g_free (block->mem);","          g_free (block);","          free_list = g_list_delete_link (free_list, l);","        }","              ","      l = next;","    }","  }"],"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There is a temptation to use [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.main_depth","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] to solve","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"problems with reentrancy. For instance, while waiting for data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to be received from the network in response to a menu item,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the menu item might be selected again. It might seem that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"one could make the menu item’s callback return immediately","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and do nothing if [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.main_depth","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] returns a value greater than 1."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"However, this should be avoided since the user then sees selecting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the menu item do nothing. Furthermore, you’ll find yourself adding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these checks all over your code, since there are doubtless many,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"many things that the user could do. Instead, you can use the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"following techniques:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk_widget_set_sensitive()"},{"text":" or modal dialogs to prevent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the user from interacting with elements while the main"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"loop is recursing.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Avoid main loop recursion in situations where you can’t handle","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"arbitrary  callbacks. Instead, structure your code so that you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simply return to the main loop and then get called again when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"there is more work to do.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/mainDepth()"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"func","title":"mainDepth()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"mainDepth"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"roleHeading":"Function","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib9mainDepthSiyF"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"title":"MainContext","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/mainDepth()":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"mainDepth()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/mainDepth()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maindepth()","abstract":[{"text":"Returns the depth of the stack of calls to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.dispatch"},{"type":"text","text":"] on any "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":" in the current thread."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"mainDepth"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}]}}}